    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. DUNCAN:H.R. 153.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8, Clause 4 grants Congress the rightto set forth rules for Naturalization; Article I, Section 8,Clause 18 grants Congress the duty to make Laws that arenecessary and proper for for Executing it's powers. Sincejurisdictions declaring themselves to be sanctuary areoperating in a lawless manner, it is necessary and proper tobring them back into line.[Page H215]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
    <summaries>
